CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1958, pg. A3 reads: "Lutherans Confer - During the recent meeting of the Eastern District of the Lutheran Church, Missouri Synod, at Chatham College, Miss Rosa J. Young, seated, center, a pioneer Lutheran missionary of Selma, Ala., held a sideline conference with local Lutheran leaders. Left to right: Mrs. John Fey, the Rev. John Fey, pastor of Faith Lutheran Church, and Mrs. Bernice D. Stewart, extreme right.  Mmes. Fey and Stewart were official delegates from Faith Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lutheran missionary Rosa J. Young wearing dark lace floral dress with corsage, seated in interior in Chatham College for Lutheran Church conference
